{"id":"d=origam-topic-3916//p=9c0eb92dd2674c9ea787fb0dd3fca17c","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3916"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["bea8544a57244682a0d19ab5e1874a2a"],"__file_part":["051876b3d8f44dc6830b9e317c9a2323"],"__part_n":["1"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3916"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-work-with-the-client-application/3916"],"title":["How to work with the client application"],"imagesFound":["7"],"imagesDescribed":["7"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/777717b12dd9ebfc92e74ffbd2e280c0080e5e95.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8225d2672b2547f1b58d26374a4492a62e01d535.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/594dd4613ebbe10c608753e5fcbac6ad3b081613.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5a431050f2bb28017fd50f76b29982dd4de5bfa6.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3405a8217e7abe20ba2b3bae0cf1f71d6526af03.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e77c5f9a44dfce00dd441ca39597ce9cadb209e0.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/09b8cbf14306f1725c8c25b83f9b96a76a26ca23.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"de5bfa6.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for the Origam application. The left sidebar features sections labeled \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 and \u0022Menu,\u0022 with various subcategories under \u0022Settings,\u0022 \u0022Maps,\u0022 and \u0022Users \u0026 Security.\u0022 Specific items include \u0022General,\u0022 \u0022Map Configuration,\u0022 \u0022Map Layers,\u0022 \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Add User,\u0022 \u0022Application Roles,\u0022 \u0022My User Profile,\u0022 \u0022User Permissions Overview,\u0022 \u0022User Roles,\u0022 and \u0022Users.\u0022 At the top right, there is a user icon displaying \u0022VT\u0022 and the name \u0022Ter Viktor.\u0022 The main area appears empty, indicating a space for content or features related to the selected menu option.\n\n\n  \n The application is brand new and empty, but there are some default settings and data like, for example: \n Menu - Settings / General / Languages \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3405a8217e7abe20ba2b3bae0cf1f71d6526af03.png]\nDescription: The interface shown represents the \u0022Languages\u0022 section of the Origam application. The left panel includes options for \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 \u0022Menu,\u0022 \u0022Settings,\u0022 \u0022General,\u0022 \u0022Features,\u0022 and \u0022Languages.\u0022 The main content area displays a table labeled \u0022Languages,\u0022 which includes two columns: \u0022Name\u0022 and \u0022IETF Tag.\u0022 The visible entries are \u0022English (US)\u0022 with the IETF tag \u0022en-US,\u0022 \u0022\u010Ce\u0161tina\u0022 with \u0022cs-CZ,\u0022 \u0022Deutsch (Deutschland)\u0022 with \u0022de-DE,\u0022 and \u0022Deutsch (Schweiz)\u0022 with \u0022de-CH.\u0022 There are additional controls at the top of the table, including buttons for adding, removing, and refreshing entries. The purpose of this interface is to manage language settings within the Origam application.\n\n\n  \n Menu - Settings / Users \u0026 Security / Users \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e77c5f9a44dfce00dd441ca39597ce9cadb209e0.png]\nDescription: The image presents a user interface for the Origam application, specifically the \u0022Users\u0022 section within the \u0022Users \u0026 Security\u0022 menu. The interface includes a table with columns labeled \u0022Shortcut,\u0022 \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022First Name,\u0022 \u0022Login Name,\u0022 \u0022Login E-mail,\u0022 and \u0022Avatar,\u0022 where several user entries are listed. Visible users include \u0022Anonymous User,\u0022 \u0022Architect (HP-BOOK-VIKTOR\\victo),\u0022 \u0022ORIGAM Server,\u0022 and \u0022Ter Viktor,\u0022 along with their respective login details. The sidebar menu contains options such as \u0022Serial Number Ranges,\u0022 \u0022System Colors,\u0022 \u0022Work Queues,\u0022 \u0022Map Configuration,\u0022 \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Add User,\u0022 \u0022Application Roles,\u0022 \u0022User Permissions Overview,\u0022 and \u0022User Roles.\u0022 There are also buttons for saving, refreshing, confirming emails, and managing two-factor authentication. The purpose of the interface is to manage user accounts and roles within the application.\n\n\n  \n Also, items like  Add User  or  My User Profile  may be useful for you. You can also add any of the menu items into Favourites. \n   Common functionality \n Now let\u2019s have a look at the basic navigation elements and page functions: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/09b8cbf14306f1725c8c25b83f9b96a76a26ca23.png]\nDescription: The interface displayed is part of the Origam application, specifically the \u0022System Colors\u0022 section. The left panel includes a menu with options such as \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 and various settings, including \u0022Features,\u0022 \u0022Languages,\u0022 and \u0022System Colors.\u0022 The main content area shows a table titled \u0022System Colors\u0022 with columns for \u0022Name,\u0022 \u0022Color,\u0022 and \u0022Description,\u0022 detailing items such as \u0022--background1\u0022 to \u0022--error1.\u0022 At the top, there are buttons for \u0022Save,\u0022 \u0022Refresh,\u0022 \u0022Search,\u0022 and user options. Navigation controls indicate a total of 20 records, with options to \u0022Export to Excel,\u0022 \u0022Column Configuration,\u0022 and \u0022Show Record Information\u0022 available. The interface is designed for managing and configuring system color settings.\n\n\n  \n More information about the client application content and ready-made building blocks can be found in this  article . \n Now you can play with the application and then start to add your own content like new screens, functionality, menu items, etc.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:40:20"},"vector":[-0.02169042,-0.002382916,-0.059395812,-0.0038552019,0.0038586822,-0.010553723,0.01691263,-0.017434293,0.008387616,-0.00800579,0.015947832,-0.02409619,0.020784503,0.016979137,0.01581446,0.0060126656,0.022953263,0.01746363,0.010137963,0.024037497,0.0020682123,-0.011102643,0.015970288,0.013428989,0.008078868,0.032049626,-0.0015003058,-0.051576316,-0.013172662,0.012916206,0.02856451,-0.07476141,-0.018619591,-0.004888909,-0.028458223,-0.0037683987,0.008015793,0.011211078,-0.037639212,0.013527523,-0.012669265,-0.020342644,-0.024607759,0.032831177,-0.006093049,-0.055010673,0.015628988,0.0075507644,-0.005112922,-0.04608294,-0.019064236,-0.0349368,0.032691695,-0.025681598,-0.0008841302,0.06400279,-0.029426018,-0.014384432,-0.03047012,0.017231887,-0.019481027,-0.00015715268,-0.022612011,-0.055188254,-7.0538445E-05,0.030511428,-0.021884248,0.014968753,-0.028729888,-0.0054778783,-0.021623017,0.025920685,-0.06380398,-0.045581404,-0.08460211,0.02335119,-0.029793993,0.011646592,-0.0020767841,0.033182543,-0.02520822,0.021914966,0.04565086,0.016163653,0.028343523,0.03205776,-0.018162016,0.09673069,0.0004928049,0.036684282,-0.060219865,-0.013113507,0.07535017,-0.040331267,-0.038239174,-0.011526847,-0.0146406805,-0.009857991,-0.000119407545,-0.027897056,-0.027755342,-0.007547112,-0.030253064,0.0053123194,0.005100859,-0.016852941,0.026518667,-0.0004583769,-0.0069226804,-0.036745314,0.00886535,-0.0009726,0.024000812,-0.022669995,0.011137594,-0.0076463786,-0.00086099515,-0.038860105,-0.035683677,0.026855867,-0.030898318,0.024948379,0.037907965,-0.03149798,-0.013235235,0.0106799295,-0.026413798,0.01709093,0.030584116,0.021705553,0.034872223,0.004599133,-0.017659182,